4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, a city council may
6 establish a board of water and sewer commissioners to
7 administer water and sewer systems for the city.
8 This bill would prohibit these boards from
9 restricting public recreation uses of a water body
10 owned or controlled by the board unless a substantial
11 public interest in doing so is demonstrated.
12 This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
13 technical revisions to update the existing code
14 language to current style.
15
16
17
18 A BILL
19 TO BE ENTITLED
20 AN ACT
21
22 Relating to boards of water and sewer commissioners; to
23 amend Section 11-50-343, Code of Alabama 1975; to prohibit the
24 boards from restricting public recreational uses of owned or
25 controlled water bodies unless a substantial public interest
26 in doing so is demonstrated; and to make nonsubstantive,
27 technical revisions to update the existing code language to
28 current style.
