121 (c)(1) A board may restrict the public's recreational
122 use of, or close, a water body or portion thereof owned or
123 controlled by the board only upon providing evidence at a
124 public hearing conducted by the board demonstrating a
125 substantial public interest exists that requires restricting
126 or closing of the water body. The board shall notify the
127 public of the hearing at least 10 days before the hearing.
128 (2) The board may restrict the public's recreational
129 use of, or close, a water body or portion thereof owned or
130 controlled by the board for 90 days without conducting a
131 public hearing if, in the determination of the board, an
132 emergency exists that necessitates the restriction or closure.
133 After 90 days, the board shall conduct a public hearing as
134 provided for in subdivision (1).
135 (3) All restrictions or closures of a water body
136 pursuant to this subsection may be appealed to the circuit
137 court having jurisdiction over the county in which the board's
138 principle place of business is located.
139 (4) This subsection shall only apply to navigable
140 waterways within 50 miles of the Gulf of America which serve
